(Corrects company name in first paragraph.)  The Federal Communications Commission
is investigating Verizon Wireless for what the company has
estimated is $50 million in overcharges to its customers.  The investigation into the charges assessed to 15 million
customers began about 10 months, the FCC said in an e-mailed
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
